#
# PURPOSE:
#     301 redirect map for shift-work.com on Render.
#     Maps legacy WordPress-era URLs (pre-April-2026 site) to their
#     closest equivalents on the current static site. This recovers
#     link equity from old URLs still in Google's index and clears
#     stale search results (which carried the old phone number).
#
# FORMAT (Render static site redirect rules):
#     /source-path  /destination-path  301
#     - One rule per line, whitespace separated.
#     - Rules are evaluated top to bottom; FIRST MATCH WINS.
#     - A trailing /* wildcard matches everything under a directory.
#     - Specific rules MUST appear before their section's wildcard
#       catch-all. Do not reorder.
#     - Each exact page has two rules (with and without trailing
#       slash) so matching works regardless of how the old URL was
#       indexed.
#
# DEPLOYMENT:
#     Place in the ROOT of the Shiftwork-Solutions-Website GitHub
#     repo. Render reads it automatically on deploy.
#
# MAINTENANCE:
#     If Google Search Console later reveals additional indexed
#     legacy URLs that 404, add specific rules for them ABOVE the
#     relevant catch-all.
#
# CHANGE LOG:
#     2026-06-11 — FULL REBUILD. Previous file contained a stale
#                  copy of sitemap.xml (April 19 version) and zero
#                  redirect rules — it was doing nothing. Replaced
#                  with a complete 301 map covering all legacy
#                  WordPress URLs captured from the old site's
#                  navigation: /shift-issues/, /news/, /about/
#                  children, /how-we-work/, /home/, quiz,
#                  calculators, and project-manager pages, plus
#                  wildcard catch-alls for old blog/category paths.
#                  NOTE: same-day host flip in Render — bare domain
#                  (shift-work.com) is now primary; www redirects
#                  to it. These rules are path-based and host-
#                  independent.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

